description:
100-Page special of Astounding Action-Packed Arachnid-Adventure! Only 3.50!

Spider-Verse continues!

What are the secrets of the mysterious scroll and what is Uncle Ben hiding? Meanwhile, Solus, Lord of The Inheritors, decrees 'Spider-Men No More!"

Plus, Spider UK goes in search of Anansi, the Spider-God. Meanwhile, on Earth 138 Spider-Punk takes on Oscorp and V.E.N.O.M.!

Also, in the near-future, Venom returns! But who is wearing the sinister symbiote?!!

Finally, its Halloween and the Wall-Crawler encounters the new villains in town The Furious Five (no, not the guys from Kung Fu Panda)!!

By Dan Slott, Guiseppe Camuncoli, Kathryn Immonen, David Lafuente, Jed Mackay Sheldon Vella, Kris Anka, Ty Templeton, Sean Ryan, In-Hyuk Lee, Bill Hader, Seth Meyers and Kevin Maguire!

Includes material reprinted from Amazing Spider-Man #13, Spider-Verse #2, 100th Anniversary Special Spider-Man #1 and Amazing Spider-Man: The Short Halloween.

description: Keira and Albert investigate the mansion of the renegade mage, Clious, only to discover that Clious is dabbling in magics no mage is allowed to dabble in (hence 'renegade'), and they discover his intern is far, far more powerful and mysterious than any intern has a right to be.

Two thousand pilgrims, two thousand suspects! A meticulous investigation in a desert and most dangerous country!

In the cold region of small Gottland, the Master Inquisitor Nikolai and his elf Boldween make a macabre discovery: a body is frozen in the ice. The link is quickly made between the victim

and the sacred pilgrimage of the Blue Dragon. The Inquisitor decides to trap the culprit and mingles amongst the travellers. The enquiry stagnates and other murders are added to the first one

The murderer is hiding in the middle of two thousand pilgrims, and his motive remains a mystery!
name: Nikola

description:
76 pages of Marvel Universe adventure on sale 22nd October!

An 'Original Sin' chapter! Daredevil is reunited with his mother as she faces Wakandan justice! By Mark Waid and Javier Rodriguez!

The Silver Surfer and Dawn begin their journey through the stars and clash with the evil Cap'n Sharrr! Cosmic adventure by Dan Slott and Michael Allred!

The Invisible Girl meets an unwelcome party-crasher in 'Love and the Space Phantom' by Jamie Hernandez!

An 'Original Sin' chapter! The Watchers gather as the final secret is revealed! Don't miss this saga's stunning conclusion by Jason Aaron and Mike Deodato!

Featuring material first printed in Daredevil #6, Marvel Now Point One #1, Strange Tales II #2 and Original Sin #8.

description: Originally appearing in 1997 this is the first issue of the Webwitch! Nina had a happy life before her encounter with the deadly Spider-Nation. Now infused with alien DNA she has been turned into a monster set upon unleashing the hordes of alien creatures upon an unsuspecting humanity. Originally presented in Webwitch #0.

Nina has been transformed into a Webwitch - the sensual wepon of the Spider-Nation. Now as humanity discovers the alien threat in their midst, she sets her sights on finding a mate to create a Spider-Nation king and usher in the rebirth of the alien race. Originally presented in Webwitch #1.

The human race is doomed as a Spider-Nation king is born. Now with the military closing in on her, Nina must unite the king and queen in a last ditch effort for the alien race to escape the artic prison they inhabit and begin a new reign upon the world. Originally presented in Webwitch #2.

All out war has been declared as the Spider-Nation attempts to once again spread their influence over the world. Nina has delivered a king to her web queen but can they escape the relentless pursuit of the military as they attempt to prevent a mating of the alien species? Originally presented in Webwitch War Prelude.

Legendary cheesecake artist Bill Maus delivers a new chapter of alien seduction as the webwitch heeds the call of her xenomorphic DNA by defending the Spider-Nation lair and forcing the military to find an extreme solution to the infestation. Originally presented in Webwitch War #1.

description:
Alluring creatures of legend come to horrifying life in this collection of full-color works of art by cult indy comic artist Mike Wolfer and colorist Ceci de la Cruz! For the first time in his 29-year career, Wolfer has a pin-up book devoted solely to his work, and dedicated to his unique brand of supernatural heroines and villainesses from the pages of Daughters of the Dark Oracle, Widow, and beyond! Also available with a nude cover.

Note: The digital edition (August 2015) for this issue was released before the print edition.

Thirty years later, comics legends Roy Thomas and Dick Giordano reunite to at last complete their unfinished B&W ink-wash adaptation of Bram Stoker's classic tale of vampire horror, Dracula, in this lush keepsake edition! Originally serialized in Marvel horror magazines VAMPIRE TALES and LEGION OF MONSTERS, their meticulous retelling of Bram Stoker's tale of Gothic horror has been found in the Marvel tombs, and will at last be unleashed upon the daylight! Collects STOKER'S DRACULA #1-4.
name: Stoker's Dracula

description: Strasbourg in the near future... or the immediate past. Whatever. An HRM virus transmitted sexually or by blood transfusion is the latest crisis. Enormous amounts of patients only adds to the climate of panic and insecurity. Professor Morin, hated by his peers and loved by the press, is developing a vaccine...
name: Intgrale

description:
The man in the iron mask! Born of humble parentage in the tiny Balkan nation of Latveria, Victor von Doom suffered hardship and loss that left him with two things: a severely disfigured face, and a deathless desire to crush all of humanity and rule the world! The self-proclaimed Dr. Doom rose quickly and violently to power in his homeland, which serves as the base of operations for his relentless crusade for world domination. The armored super-villain will stop at nothing to achieve his goal, leaving devastation and despair in his wake. Such is the VILLAINY OF DR. DOOM!

Collects Fantastic Four Vol. 1 #39-40, 84-87, 239-240, and Fantastic Four Annual #2.

Note: Printing error. This trade paperback doesn't contain #239-240. It actually contains #246-247.

name: Las Armas vivientes

description: Having arrived on Rubanis and broke, Valrian and Laureline would be hard to imagine they are going to leave rich. But anything can happen in this messy megalopolis. Colonel Tlocq, rotten police chief offers them a small job: have a look into the circle of power which controls this mess of a planet. But who or what is responsible?
name: El Circulo del poder

description: Valerian and Laureline spend a dream holiday in one of the tourist paradises of the cosmos. But it isn't certain they'll have much fun in their palace. Billionaires such as the sometimes obnoxious Great Caliph Iksaladam is there with his harem and his Califon.
name: Rehenes de Ultralum

description: Touring an Earth colony on Alflolol, Valrian and Laureline meet the real inhabitants of the place, who went on a small 4000-year tour: Argol, Garol, Orgal, Logar and their pet Goumoun. They discover that the Earthlings have settled on what was previously their camp. It's the beginning of a confrontation between the disorder of the Alflololiens and the effectiveness of the governor from Earth.
name: Bienvenue sur Aflolol

description: Valrian, space-time agent, and Laureline crash on an unknown planet and are captured. They discover that the population of this planet is enslaved and starved by a mysterious entity called "the Master," forcing inhabitants and prisoners to work to exhaustion, under the threat of his terrible birds, whose bite causes madness.
name: Les Oiseaux du matre
